### Description

Currently the `KeycloakMetricsHandler` is bound with a strict path binding to `/metrics`. 
This works fine with the default context-path of `/` however, when a different context-path is configured the `/metrics` endpoint doesn't work anymore and only returns an error message.

If we enable metrics via `-Dkc.metrics.enabled=true` and configure a custom context-path via `-Dquarkus.http.root-path=/auth`, we see the following error response returned if the `/auth/metrics` endpoint is accessed:
```
The expected context root of metrics is /metrics, but a request with a different path was routed to MetricsRequestHandler
```

The problem is that the `org.keycloak.quarkus.runtime.services.health.KeycloakMetricsHandler` is configured with a fixed `/metrics` path which is used to check an incoming request.



### Discussion

_No response_

### Motivation

To remain compatible with older Keycloak deployments, we want to use the custom context-path `/auth`. At the same time we also want metrics to be available out of the box.

### Details

A small fix is to make `KeycloakMetricsHandler` aware of the configured context path:
```
package org.keycloak.quarkus.runtime.services.health;

import io.quarkus.smallrye.metrics.runtime.SmallRyeMetricsHandler;
import org.keycloak.quarkus.runtime.configuration.Configuration;

import static org.keycloak.quarkus.runtime.configuration.MicroProfileConfigProvider.NS_QUARKUS_PREFIX;

public class KeycloakMetricsHandler extends SmallRyeMetricsHandler {

    public static final String DEFAULT_METRICS_ENDPOINT = "/metrics";

    public KeycloakMetricsHandler() {
        String contextPathPrefix = Configuration.getOptionalValue(NS_QUARKUS_PREFIX.concat("http.root-path")).orElse("");
        String metricsPath = (contextPathPrefix + DEFAULT_METRICS_ENDPOINT).replaceAll("//","/");
        setMetricsPath(metricsPath);
    }
}

```
